{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Enable one parent to change their child's name if the other parent is absent",
        "additional_details": "My children have absent fathers but because they still have parental responsibility I cannot change their name without the father\u2019s consent. I\u2019d like to be able to change their name without having to get in contact with the fathers and ask for their permission, as they haven\u2019t been involved in their upbringing or even helped with child maintenance. I\u2019ve brought them up on my own, and feel I shouldn\u2019t have to consult an absent parent on changing their names. ",
        "background": "I would like it to be possible for a resident parent to change their child\u2019s name without the permission of the other parent, or needing to get a court order, if the other parent has been absent from the child\u2019s life for more than 5 years.",
